  "text": "Round of 16 · 4 July 2026 · Houston. Final score: Canada 0–3 Morocco. Morocco marched into the last eight and ended the co-hosts' dream on home soil.\n\nFor Canada, one of three host nations, this was the end of a home World Cup; for Morocco, a fourth straight knockout scalp and a statement of intent.\n\nThe goals, in sequence: 50′ Azzedine Ounahi — 0–1; 82′ Azzedine Ounahi — 0–2; 98′ Soufiane Rahimi — 0–3. That is 3 goals in all, Canada accounting for 0 and Morocco 3.\n\nAzzedine Ounahi took over after the interval, first curling home a right-footed shot through traffic after a clever Achraf Hakimi free-kick, then punishing a stretched Canadian back line for his second. Substitute Soufiane Rahimi, released by Brahim Díaz, made the win emphatic deep into stoppage time. Canada huffed and puffed in front of their own crowd but never truly troubled the Moroccan defence. Morocco, the surprise semi-finalists of 2022, again looked like the tournament's great disruptors.\n\nMomentum, as ever in the knockouts, proved a fragile and fleeting thing.\n\nThe expected-goals picture tightened around every set piece and transition.\n\nFor the record, Morocco advanced. Goal, team and minute for every event above are Merkle-proven on Solana devnet via TxLINE; the scorer names are attributed from public match reports and aligned to the verified goals by team and order. Nothing here rests on the commentator's word alone.",
